text: Yousef Abdelrahman Yousef Abu Jalboush (; born 15 June 1998), sometimes known as Sisa, is a Jordanian professional football player. He plays as an attacking midfielder for Jordanian Pro League side Al-Hussein and the Jordan national team. == International career == He was called up to the Jordan first team for the first time in a friendly match that ended in a 2-0 victory over Tajikistan on February 1, 2021. He was also called up to national team for the 2023 AFC Asian Cup. In 24 February, 2024, Jordan defeat by Qatar and results 3-1 in 2023 AFC Asian Cup Final. == Personal life == Abu Jalboush was given the nickname Sissa as a child by his father, who was called “Abu Sissa” by his friends. == Achievements == ;Al-Faisaly SC *Jordanian Pro League: 2018–19, 2022 *Jordan FA Cup: 2018–19, 2021 *Jordan Shield Cup: 2022, 2023 *Jordan Super Cup: 2017, 2020 == References == == Other websites == * Category:Pages with unreviewed translations Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:NFT template using Wikidata
